SYNOPSIS
	string pad( string text, int width)
	string pad( string text, int width, int padchar)
	string pad( int number, int width)
	string pad( int number, int width, int padchar)

DESCRIPTION
	pseudofun:	justified_text pad( text, +/-len, padchar);

	Format and justify the string 'text'. If 'number' is given, then
	'number' is first converted to a string and then padded.
	The absolute value of 'width' specifies the length of the justified
	return string.
	The text is
		left-justified when 'width' is positive
		right-justified when 'width' is negative
	Default 'padchar' is ' ' (space).

EXAMPLES
	pad( "Balowski", 10);      /* result: "Balowski  " */
	pad( "Balowski", -10);     /* result: "  Balowski" */
	pad( 200, -5);             /* result: "  200" */
	pad( "", 8, '-');          /* result: "--------" */
	pad( "Whatever", +/-4);    /* result: "What" */
	pad( "asfd", 0);           /* result: "" */

SEE ALSO
	format(E), print(E)
